5.1 Definition: Category of structured intelligence governance
The category (“Category Theory” 2025) 𝒢\mathcal G of structured intelligence governance is isomorphic to K2K_2 cycle with loops comprising:

Objects 𝚘𝚋(𝒢)={H,A}\mathtt{ob}(\mathcal G) = \{H, A \}:

HH from the humans in the nodes of SS;
AA from the automata in the nodes of SS.

Morphisms 𝚑𝚘𝚖(𝒢)\mathtt{hom}(\mathcal G):

HHHH: humans interact or self-reflect;
HAHA: humans instantiate intent on automata;
AAAA: automata stack without human intervention;
AHAH: automata output with constraints

Governance constraint measures assign one of the four levels of emergence (expected, violation, miscreant, virtuous) to both the objects and the morphisms.
